# Standard Project Structure

## Organization Principles

### By Feature (Feature-based)
Organize code by functionality/domain, not by file type.

```
src/
├── auth/
│   ├── auth.service.ts
│   ├── auth.controller.ts
│   ├── auth.types.ts
│   └── auth.test.ts
├── users/
│   ├── user.service.ts
│   ├── user.controller.ts
│   └── user.types.ts
└── shared/
    ├── utils/
    ├── types/
    └── constants/
```

### By Layer (Layer-based)
Alternative for larger projects or when architecture requires clear separation.

```
src/
├── domain/
│   ├── entities/
│   ├── repositories/
│   └── services/
├── infrastructure/
│   ├── database/
│   ├── api/
│   └── external/
├── application/
│   ├── use-cases/
│   └── dto/
└── presentation/
    ├── controllers/
    ├── views/
    └── components/
```

## Standard Structure for Web Projects

```
project-root/
├── src/
│   ├── app/              # Main application (Next.js, etc)
│   ├── components/       # Reusable components
│   ├── lib/              # Libraries and utilities
│   ├── hooks/            # Custom hooks (React)
│   ├── types/            # Type definitions
│   ├── config/           # Configuration
│   └── styles/           # Global styles
├── public/               # Static files
├── tests/                # Integration/E2E tests
├── docs/                 # Documentation
├── scripts/              # Build/deploy scripts
├── .env.example          # Environment variables template
├── .gitignore
├── README.md
└── package.json
```

## Standard Structure for APIs

```
api/
├── src/
│   ├── routes/           # API routes
│   ├── controllers/      # Control logic
│   ├── services/         # Business logic
│   ├── models/           # Data models
│   ├── middleware/       # Middlewares
│   ├── utils/            # Utilities
│   └── config/           # Configuration
├── tests/
├── migrations/           # Database migrations
└── README.md
```

## Standard Structure for Venture Builder Projects

Every project created through the venture builder workflow must follow this structure:

```
projects/[project-name]/
├── documents/                              # Strategic documents (ALWAYS present)
│   ├── product-strategy-[project-name].md # Business strategy and vision
│   ├── prd-[project-name].md              # Product requirements document
│   ├── analytics-events-[project-name].csv # Analytics event catalog (recommended)
│   ├── marketing-guide-[project-name].md  # Marketing and communication guide
│   ├── design-system-[project-name].md   # Visual design system
│   ├── user-research.md                   # Optional: user research
│   └── README.md                          # Documents index and structure
├── src/                          # Application code (created when needed)
│   ├── components/              # Reusable components
│   ├── pages/                   # Page components
│   ├── lib/                     # Libraries and utilities
│   ├── hooks/                   # Custom hooks (React)
│   ├── types/                   # Type definitions
│   ├── config/                  # Configuration
│   └── styles/                  # Global styles
├── public/                       # Static assets
├── README.md                     # Project overview
└── [config files]                # package.json, tailwind.config.ts, etc.
```

**Critical Requirements:**
- Every project MUST have a `documents/` folder
- Minimum required documents: `product-strategy-[project-name].md`, `prd-[project-name].md`, `design-system-[project-name].md`
- Recommended documents: `analytics-events-[project-name].csv` (for analytics tracking)
- **Naming Convention:** All standard documents follow the pattern `[document-type]-[project-name].md` (or `.csv` for analytics events) to avoid conflicts when working with multiple projects
- Documents folder structure is standardized across all projects
- Design system document drives visual consistency through workspace-level rules
- Analytics Event Catalog enables KPI tracking and follows Analytics Tracking Standard
- Project folder name should be in kebab-case (e.g., `my-awesome-business`)

**Workflow:**
1. `/start-a-business` creates project structure and `documents/` folder
2. Product Strategy is created first in `documents/product-strategy-[project-name].md`
3. PRD is created based on Product Strategy in `documents/prd-[project-name].md`
4. Analytics Event Catalog is created based on PRD KPIs in `documents/analytics-events-[project-name].csv` (recommended)
5. Marketing Guide is created based on Product Strategy in `documents/marketing-guide-[project-name].md`
6. Design System is created based on Product Strategy + PRD in `documents/design-system-[project-name].md`
7. Design System automatically generates `src/index.css` and `tailwind.config.ts`

## Naming Conventions

### Directories
- Use kebab-case: `user-profile`, `api-client`
- Use camelCase for React component directories: `UserProfile`

**Note:** For file naming conventions, see `code-style.mdc`.

## Configuration Files

Keep at project root:
- `.env.example` - Environment variables template
- `.gitignore` - Files ignored by Git
- `.editorconfig` - Editor configuration
- `README.md` - Main documentation
- `LICENSE` - Project license

## Separation of Concerns

- **Services**: Pure business logic
- **Controllers**: Coordination between requests and services
- **Models/Entities**: Data structure
- **Utils/Helpers**: Helper functions without business dependencies
- **Types**: Type and interface definitions
